canonical:
  title: 謝改職狀
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 右某伏蒙仁恩特賜公牒改署舘驛廵官令隨旌旆西去者雖命重難荷而身輕欲飛稱心懷捧檄之榮滿口詠從軍之樂唯慙幽劣有辱奬怜感恩而旣識海深擧步而但憂冰薄况無孫搴之精騎自比顔峻之小兒將何以剖析事機游敭德業然所願者得睹龍飛玉劒豹掣牙旗風雷振大捷之聲日月照中興之運則某也有望於一言長價或爲天上之人萬里從知免作池中之物行唯踴躍坐則禱祠下情無任榮抃兢灼之至
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝改職狀
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 右某伏蒙仁恩。特賜公牒。改署舘驛廵官。令隨旌旆西去者。雖命重難荷。而身輕欲飛。稱心懷捧檄之榮。滿口詠從軍之樂。唯慙幽劣。有辱奬怜。感恩而旣識海深。擧步而但憂冰薄。况無孫搴之精騎。自比顔峻之小兒。將何以剖析事機。游敭德業。然所願者得睹龍飛玉劒。豹掣牙旗。風雷振大捷之聲。日月照中興之運。則某也有望於一言長價。或爲天上之人。萬里從知。免作池中之物。行唯踴躍。坐則禱祠。下情無任榮抃兢灼之至。
korean:
  title: 사 개직 장
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: 모(某)는 엎드려 인은(仁恩)을 입어, 특히 공첩(公牒)을 내리어 관역순관(館驛巡官)의 직을 고치고 정패(旌旆)를 따라 서쪽으로 떠나라는 처분을 받았습니다.비록 명령은 무거워 짊어지기 어려우나, 몸은 가벼워 날 듯하며, 마음먹은 그대로 봉격(捧檄)의 영광을 입었고, 입이 닳도록 종군(從軍)의 악(樂)을 읊조리게 되었으니, 오직 용렬한 자질이라, 추앙해 주시는 성의에 욕되는 것이 부끄러우며, 은혜를 느낌이 이미 바다같이 깊음을 인식하고 한 발자국만 옮겨도 다만 엷은 얼음을 밟는 것같이 두렵습니다. 하물며 손건(孫搴)의 날랜 기병(騎兵)이 없어 스스로 안준(顔峻)의 작은 아이에 비하는 처지에 있는데 어떻게 해서 사리를 분석하고 덕업(德業)을 선양하겠습니까.그러나 원하는 것은, 용의 옥검(玉劍)을 날리고 표범의 아기(牙旗)를 끌면서 바람과 우레는 승첩의 소리를 떨치고, 해와 달은 중흥의 운수에 비치는 것을 얻어보게 되면, 저같은 사람도 한 마디 말에 값이 올라 혹시 천상(天上)의 인물이 되고, 만리에 지기(知己)를 따라 못 속에 고기 되는 신세를 면할 희망을 가지고 있게 되니, 다닐 적에는 기뻐서는 날뛰고, 앉으면 빌고 빌겠습니다. 하정(下情)에 너무도 영광스럽고 송구합니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0500_010_0170&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Memorial of Gratitude for a Transferred Post
  author: Choe Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your humble servant bows in deep gratitude for the benevolence bestowed upon him. A public decree has been graciously issued, promoting him to the post of Inspector of the Relay Stations, commanding him to follow the banners westward. Though the mandate weighs heavy and strains the shoulders, the body grows light as if ready to soar. The heart overflows with the glory of bearing such a charge, and from his lips flows endless praise for the honor of serving in the field. Yet he is ashamed of his own meager talents, unworthy of such esteemed regard. The debt of gratitude runs as deep as the ocean, and with each step forward he treads as though upon thin ice, fearful of breaking through. How can one lacking the swift cavalry of Sun Qian, who sees himself merely as a child beside such luminaries, hope to discern the subtleties of affairs or illuminate his virtue and accomplishments?

    And yet he harbors one fervent wish: to witness the dragon's jade sword unfurled and the leopard's ivory banner streaming, while thunder and wind proclaim the voice of great victory, and sun and moon illuminate the age of restored glory. Should this come to pass, perhaps such a humble one might gain worth in a single word spoken by his sovereign, becoming a figure of the celestial realm, finding kindred spirits across ten thousand miles, and thus escape the fate of a creature trapped in a pond. Whether walking or sitting, he shall leap with joy and bow in ceaseless prayer. His heart overflows with such reverence and gratitude that words can scarcely contain it.
  footnotes:
    - Sun Qian (孫搴) was a renowned cavalry commander of antiquity, representing military excellence and strategic brilliance.
    - The contrast between 'celestial realm' and 'creature in a pond' represents the speaker's hope for elevation through distinguished service versus remaining obscure and forgotten.
    - The maritime imagery—deep oceans and thin ice—conveys both the immensity of the gratitude and the precarious nature of his position despite the honor bestowed.
